olo from the bridge at South Karana! <BR>  <BR> You may not get a lot of loot, but the exp is great. <BR>  <BR> Fight elephants, Centaur Foals, Centaur Shelties, occasional straggling Aviak Egrets and Darters, and Ghannex Drah (at the skeleton ruins). <BR>  <BR> I stayed and solo'd here for a cash cow of experience at these levels. <BR>  <BR> I also spent some time fighting Aviaks at the bird city. This can be very profitable, but you are relying on others. I've found that unless you find some really good friends that are mature in their fighting habits, you are better off relying on yourself. <BR>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Quelud Raveneye</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/7/00 10:14:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Crags</span><hr size=1> I killed Crag Spiders from lvl 21 to 24.  They are a tough battle but smart magicians can solo them without the loss of a single hitpoint.  Just make sure you have lots of malachite because your pet will get poisoned and may die.  They also give up words, runes, pages, venom sacks, and most importantly....a grip of spider silk.  Up to 6 at a time.  Tailors pay well for this and I made 2 full suits of raw silk armour with all the silk I got by killing Crags.  Then just move up to Broon.  Becareful my fellow magicians...and Good Journey. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukyranfangbreaker.showPublicProfile>Kyran Fangbreaker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/7/00 10:21:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/set/baby.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Aye</span><hr size=1> I'm tempted to take on Crags next.  I fought them a bit with my Druid, and think they would be a pushover if they didn't freaking poison you 8).  So, with a water pet and a sewing kit to make swatches I think a magician would clean up on those spiders. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=soronnfirecaller>Soronn FireCaller</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local user</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/8/00 7:37:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Crag Spiders</span><hr size=1> Remember that Water pets are best for these beasties - Water pets are immune to poison. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Morquen Elfbane</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/9/00 4:35:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   For my dark siblings...</span><hr size=1> I can't sing the praises of OOT (Ocean of Tears) enough.  Get together a group of 6 dark races of levels 20 to 24, go to the sister island, and kill the red/yellow Sister spawns at the dock, under the tree, and fishing...  They drop 1 or 2 plat, purity belts, and wood elf meat (yum!).   <BR>  <BR> Your faction with everything in the world drops.  But the Crushbone Orcs will love you ... and nobody else is there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Meneldil</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/9/00 5:49:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   treants</span><hr size=1> Well, this is all I will say, <BR> I went from level 22 to level 34 in 2 weeks at the treant spawn in South K.  It is camped now but when I was there it was not, you need a friend or two to run the spawn, but the exp is amazing (at the beginning one level a day).  If you can hit this place in the off hours you can do great. <BR>  <BR> Meneldil-MM <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> fdiwene</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/13/00 1:01:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   bards are great to kill =)</span><hr size=1> All i gotta say is Cordelia Miniester in NK, Iwent from 19 to 22 in about 9 hours. About 1-2pp loot, and some think faction sucks, but maybe it was just a glitch or something, I =with her conning indiff, and she still does. I am a high elf. VERY good xp in my opinion, i just left cause it can get a little boring, good if you just wanna lvl though. happy hunting,=) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Quale</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(3/10/00 9:19:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   things NOT to kill</span><hr size=1> I know that these strings are supposed to be helpfull, and I may not be too helpfull saying this, but someone has gotta say it. Please do not kill elephants! These magnificent animals are special.<br>
And I have seen what bad elephant karma can do to people, and it's not pretty. I dom't like to threaten anyone, but there it is.<br>
<br>
Snifnix <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Fazlano</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(3/17/00 6:01:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Where to go?</span><hr size=1> Everyone here seems to say south karana is the place to hunt now. I find it way too crowded to get any exp though. Any suggestions on where to hunt? I prefer grouping, camping an npc isn't my style. Suggestions? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Xallamandar</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(4/24/00 9:49:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re</span><hr size=1> If your hunting grounds are camped. A good place to solo from lvl 20 to 24 is the Tent terrors in Najena in the first room just past where the Ogre guards are. They drop decent loot and there are two spawns. The trick is to send your Earth pet in before the tent terror leaves the little alcove so the other one does not get pulled to early. If you kill the first one fast, the second one is no problem. Soloed a few lvls here because the server was overcamped, but it is somewhat of a slow spawn, and not a great deal else to pull.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Eloina</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(5/1/00 6:21:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.sho